The compiler doesn&#39;t analyze your for loops to make sure that `h` is always assigned within them. Therefore it doesn&#39;t know if at the point where you attempt to print `h` (`System.out.println(h)`), it has already been assigned.

This can be easily avoided by giving `h` an initial value:

    int h = 0;

